{"id":"1210.7568","submitter":"Evangelos Sfakianakis","authors":"Evangelos I. Sfakianakis","title":"Analysis of Oscillons in the SU(2) Gauged Higgs Model","comments":"35 pages, 19 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":"MIT-CTP 4412","categories":"hep-ph hep-th","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  A stable oscillon was found in the (classical) analysis of the SU(2) gauged\nHiggs model under a 2:1 ratio between the Higgs and W masses, both analytically\nand numerically. We extend these results by constructing oscillons for all\nvalues of the Higgs mass and examining their stability, finding them to be\nstable when the Higgs mass is almost equal to twice the W mass. We also\ninvestigate the dependence of the oscillon lifetime on the mass of the Higgs,\nseeing different behavior for different regions of the Higgs mass. Close to the\n2:1 mass ratio the interaction of the two fields leads to either a stable\noscillon or to its quick decay, based on its amplitude and the exact masses of\nthe fields. Moving further away from this ratio the fields seize to interact\nand the oscillon disperses. Furthermore, we show that the oscillon lifetime\nscales quadratically with the small amplitude parameter which is linked to the\nsmall amplitude expansion that we use to construct the oscillon. Finally, we\nlist all families of oscillon solutions that can be formally constructed in\nthis model and discuss their properties. The results can be easily extended to\nother composite oscillons in particle physics and beyond.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Oct 2012 05:38:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-10-31"}
{"id":"1210.7569","submitter":"John Wilmes","authors":"Madhusudan Manjunath, Frank-Olaf Schreyer, John Wilmes","title":"Minimal Free Resolutions of the $G$-parking Function Ideal and the\n  Toppling Ideal","comments":"22 pages, 3 figures; v3: minor changes","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.AC math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  The $G$-parking function ideal $M_G$ of a directed multigraph $G$ is a\nmonomial ideal which encodes some of the combinatorial information of $G$. It\nis an initial ideal of the toppling ideal $I_G$, a lattice ideal intimately\nrelated to the chip-firing game on a graph. Both ideals were first studied by\nCori, Rossin, and Salvy. A minimal free resolution for $M_G$ was given by\nPostnikov and Shaprio in the case when $G$ is saturated, i.\\,e., whenever there\nis at least one edge $(u,v)$ for every ordered pair of distinct vertices $u$\nand $v$. They also raised the problem of an explicit description of the minimal\nfree resolution in the general case. In this paper, we give a minimal free\nresolution of $M_G$ for any undirected multigraph $G$, as well as for a family\nof related ideals including the toppling ideal $I_G$. This settles a conjecture\nof Manjunath and Sturmfels, as well as a conjecture of Perkinson and Wilmes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Oct 2012 05:44:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 3 Nov 2012 02:02:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 24 Dec 2012 20:40:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-12-27"}
